21/07/25
I‚Äôm building this project while learning, so there will be regular updates and improvements as I progress. 
I expect there will be some errors and trial and error early on, but this is part of my learning process.

I‚Äôm using VS Code for the frontend design and NetBeans 25 for the backend Java development.
Keeping these separate helps me stay organised while I focus on functionality first and decide on the design later.

The initial step was to speak directly with the owner of the restaurant where I work, and explain the idea of digitising the stock system. 
The goal is to make the system accessible from anywhere
so that the owner and kitchen staff can check stock levels remotely, without needing to be physically at the restaurant.

There are currently around 99 items to be managed in the system, which I‚Äôm organising into different categories and Java classes
(e.g Meat & Seafood, Vegetables, Prepared Items). These will help structure the code in a maintainable way as the project grows.
here are the classes i have decided to group the items (objects) into:

